# Auth & subscription conventions

## Single bootstrap path for new users

**All new accounts** (email/password or Google) must be created via `createUserWithInitialData` in `lib/services/auth/user-bootstrap-service.ts`.

When adding signup paths, never call `prisma.user.create` directly elsewhere.

```typescript
// ✅ Required in createUserWithInitialData
subscriptionTier: "FREE",
```

Prisma defaults to `FREE`, but the explicit field is intentional — keep it when editing bootstrap.

## Auth response shape

`mapUserToAuthResponse` must include `user.subscriptionTier` (`FREE` | `PREMIUM`) so clients know tier immediately after login/signup.

## Google vs password

| Method | UI | API |
|--------|-----|-----|
| Email/password | `/login`, `/signup` forms | `POST /api/auth/login`, `/register` |
| Google | GSI button (`AuthSocialSection`) | `POST /api/auth/google` with `{ idToken }` |

Login/signup UI does **not** use NextAuth `signIn("google")` redirect — custom JWT routes are canonical.

## Account linking

Same email → one account. Google login links to an existing password account **without changing** `subscriptionTier` (preserve `PREMIUM` if already upgraded).

OAuth-only users (`passwordHash: null`) must reject password login with a clear Google-only message.

## Browser password save

Email/password success should call `promptSavePasswordCredential` from `lib/browser-credentials.ts`. Forms need `name` + `autoComplete` (`username`/`current-password` on login; `new-password` on signup).

## Tests to update when changing auth

- `tests/unified-auth.spec.ts` — API contracts, FREE tier, linking, premium preservation
- `tests/ci-smoke.spec.ts` — login/signup UI smoke + password E2E

Test Google tokens (`test-google:...`) work in non-production only — see `google-identity-service.ts`.

## Freemium reference

Tier rules and paywall flags: `lib/subscription.ts`, `FREEMIUM_IMPLEMENTATION.md`, `config/featureFlags.ts`.
